==English==
===Etymology===
Via Middle English and Old French from Latin [[laudare]]

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɔːd|-ɔːd]]

===Transitive verb===
'''to laud'''
# to [[praise]], to [[glorify]]
====Translations====
*German: [[preisen]]
*Telugu: [[మెచ్చుకొను]] (mecchukonu)

===Noun===
'''laud'''  (plural ''lauds'')
# praise or [[glorification]]
# a [[hymn]] of praise
#(''in plural'', sometimes ''Lauds'') a [[prayer]] [[service]] following [[matins]]

